name: First Commission Cow Painting
description: This painting was commissioned by Kem Barrett of Abbott Texas, after seeing Josephs work at an art show at Studio Gallery in Waco Texas with her mother. The painting was created from photo reference taken by Joseph out at her family farm. The painting was to live above her fire place. This was also the first time Joseph met cows...which would lead to Vibrant Cows. This painting was created and completed on canvas while he was living in Bedstuy, Brooklyn, New York...subletting a studio from artist and composer Stephan Tcherepnin
